rca_of_the_issue:
CartContext.jsx pattern:
  const [items, setItems] = useState([]);
  useEffect(()=>{ /* read from localStorage and setItems(...) */ }, []);
  useEffect(()=>{ localStorage.setItem(...JSON.stringify(items)) }, [items]);
On each fresh mount: render commits with items=[], then mount effects run in declaration order. The read effect reads the saved cart and schedules setItems(saved). The write effect fires immediately after with the still-current closure value items=[] and persists '[]' to localStorage — wiping the saved cart. The deferred re-render later writes the now-restored items back, but in practice (esp. when an unrelated component or React.StrictMode causes an extra effect cycle, or any race with cross-tab events) the cart can remain empty as observed. Mitigation: use a lazy state initializer that synchronously hydrates from localStorage on the very first render, so the write effect only ever persists the real cart.
